com.fortify.client.ssc.api.query.builder

Class AbstractSSCEntityQueryBuilder<T extends AbstractSSCEntityQueryBuilder<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.fortify.util.rest.query.AbstractRestConnectionQueryBuilder<SSCAuthenticatingRestConnection,T>
      • com.fortify.client.ssc.api.query.builder.AbstractSSCEntityQueryBuilder<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Concrete builder type
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractSSCApplicationVersionChildEntityQueryBuilder, AbstractSSCApplicationVersionsQueryBuilder, SSCApplicationsQueryBuilder, SSCArtifactByIdQueryBuilder, SSCAttributeDefinitionsQueryBuilder, SSCAuthEntitiesQueryBuilder, SSCBugTrackersQueryBuilder, SSCCustomTagsQueryBuilder, SSCIssueDetailsByIdQueryBuilder, SSCIssueTemplatesQueryBuilder, SSCJobsQueryBuilder, SSCRulepackQueryBuilder

    public abstract class AbstractSSCEntityQueryBuilder<T extends AbstractSSCEntityQueryBuilder<T>>
extends AbstractRestConnectionQueryBuilder<SSCAuthenticatingRestConnection,T>

    This abstract base class is used to build SSCEntityQuery instances. Concrete implementations will need to provide the actual SSC REST API endpoint by calling the AbstractRestConnectionQueryBuilder.appendPath(String) method (usually in their constructor), and indicate whether this endpoint supports paging (by providing the pagingSupported parameter to the constructor of this superclass).

    This class provides various protected methods for configuring common SSC request parameters, like 'fields' and 'orderBy'. Depending on whether the target SSC endpoint supports these parameters, concrete implementations can override these methods as 'public' to make the generic method available, and/or provide more specialized builder methods that call these generic methods, for example to support specific fields to be added to the 'q' parameter.

    Author:
    Ruud Senden
